<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1325,1238,1745]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,451,1358,1384]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Discussion.</emphasis>
This species was described based on two males from “Eslava, 
<collectingCountry box="[1193,1288,1359,1385]" name="Mexico" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Mexico</collectingCountry>
”, a locality that could not be found in atlases and gazetteers (Selander &amp; Vaurie 
<number box="[1168,1230,1399,1425]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1962.0">1962</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Campbell" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" refString="Campbell, J. M. (1974) A new species of Oxyporus (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) from Mexico with comments on Oxyporus elegans LeConte. The Coleopterists Bulletin, 28 (3), 155 - 157." type="journal article" year="1974">
Campbell 
<number box="[319,382,1439,1465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1974.0">1974</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). However, this locality is specified in the “Biologia Centrali­Americana” as being in the Distrito Federal, at an elevation of 
<quantity box="[833,945,1479,1505]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4384" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="ft" value="8000.0">8000 feet</quantity>
(Selander &amp; Vaurie 
<number box="[1192,1255,1479,1505]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1962.0">1962</number>
). The newly discovered female specimen confirms that 
<taxonomicName box="[855,1007,1519,1544]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxyporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="lawrencei">
<emphasis box="[855,1007,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<collectingCountry box="[855,879,1519,1544]" name="Iceland" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">O</collectingCountry>
. lawrencei
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does indeed occur in Distrito Federal. This species has also been recorded from Jalisco, 
<collectingCountry box="[1033,1125,1559,1585]" name="Mexico" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, Michoacan and Morelos (
<bibRefCitation author="Navarrete-Heredia" box="[376,732,1599,1625]" pageId="8" pageNumber="12" refString="Navarrete-Heredia, J. L., Newton, A. F., Thayer, M. K., Ashe, J. S. &amp; Chandler, D. S. (2002) Guia ilustrada para los generos de Staphylinidae (Coleoptera) de Mexico. Illustrated guide to the genera of Staphylinidae (Coleoptera) of Mexico. Universidad de Guadalajara y Conabio, Mexico, 401 pp." type="book" year="2002">
Navarrete­Heredia 
<emphasis box="[603,654,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[668,732,1599,1625]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Females of 
<taxonomicName box="[885,1035,1599,1624]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxyporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="lawrencei">
<emphasis box="[885,1035,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<collectingCountry box="[885,909,1599,1624]" name="Iceland" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">O</collectingCountry>
. lawrencei
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have not been described previously (
<bibRefCitation author="Campbell" box="[408,599,1639,1665]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" refString="Campbell, J. M. (1974) A new species of Oxyporus (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) from Mexico with comments on Oxyporus elegans LeConte. The Coleopterists Bulletin, 28 (3), 155 - 157." type="journal article" year="1974">
Campbell 
<number box="[536,599,1639,1665]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1974.0">1974</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Although our female specimen generally agrees with the original description (based on males: 
<bibRefCitation author="Campbell" box="[718,904,1679,1705]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" refString="Campbell, J. M. (1974) A new species of Oxyporus (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) from Mexico with comments on Oxyporus elegans LeConte. The Coleopterists Bulletin, 28 (3), 155 - 157." type="journal article" year="1974">
Campbell 
<number box="[842,904,1679,1705]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1974.0">1974</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), we did observe some differences which are summarized in 
<tableCitation box="[566,654,1719,1745]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="9.[264,352,283,307]" captionTargetBox="[272,1315,415,529]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="TABLE 1. Some differences and additional characters observed in the recently collected female of Oxyporus lawrencei in comparison to the original description of the species based on males (Campbell 1974)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF1166462209F710FE80FEFBFEC0FEB7" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" tableUuid="DF1166462209F710FE80FEFBFEC0FEB7">
Table 
<number box="[638,654,1719,1745]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1.0">1</number>
</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Table-UUID="DF1166462209F710FE80FEFBFEC0FEB7" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF1166462209F710FE80FEFBFEC0FEB7" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" targetBox="[272,1315,415,529]" targetIsTable="true" targetPageId="9">
